Class TestDefException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • com.itko.lisa.test.LisaException
          • com.itko.lisa.test.TestDefException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class TestDefException
extends LisaException
    This is the base exception class for all LISA test definition errors. If there is an exception related to the test case itself, then a TestDefException is thrown. For example, trying to reference a data set that was not defined would throw this type of exception. The complement to this exception on the test execution side is the TestRunException
    See Also:
    TestRunException, Serialized Form
